@Node "Introduction" "RxAsl Introduction"

  @{u}@{b}Introduction@{ub}@{uu}


    The library is a set of function to manipulate asl.library
    requesters. The library offers supports for asl.library V44
    (AmigaOS 3.5) end V45 (AmigaOS 3.9).

@EndNode

@Node "Author" "RxAsl Author"

  @{u}@{b}Author@{ub}@{uu}


    I am Alfonso Ranieri

    My e-mail address is alforan@tin.it

    You can find last version of this library at my home page:
    http://digilander.libero.it/asoft/

@EndNode

@Node "WRID" "RxAsl Warning, Requirements, Installation and Distribution"

  @{u}@{b}Warning, Requirements, Installation and Distribution@{ub}@{uu}


    @{u}Warning@{uu}
    THIS SOFTWARE AND INFORMATION ARE PROVIDED "AS IS". ALL USE
    IS AT YOUR OWN RISK, AND NO LIABILITY OR RESPONSIBILITY IS
    ASSUMED. NO WARRANTIES ARE MADE.

    @{u}Requirements@{uu}
    The library needs AmigaOS, version 3 or higher.

    Installation
    Use the installation script.

    @{u}Distribution@{uu}
    RxAsl is FreeWare
    You are free to distribute it as long as the original archive
    is kept intact. Commercial use or its inclusion in other
    software package is prohibited without prior written consents
    from the Author.

@EndNode

@Node "Terms" "RxAsl Terms"

  @{b}Terms@{ub}


    The main terms used are:

    o stem or stemName: a valid ARexx variable name e.g. var,
      var.0, var.name

    o type of fields:
      . S   a string
      . N   an integral number
      . B   a boolean
      . M   a number or a string

    o types of function arguments:
      . D   any data            --
      . N   numeric             /N
      . S   symbol              /S ARexx valid symbol
      . V   stemName            /V ARexx valid symbol as S but
                                 with length<20

@EndNode

@Node "Bugs" "RxAsl Bugs"

  @{b}Bugs@{ub}


    None knows.

@EndNode

@Node "Functions" "RxAsl Functions"

  @{u}@{b}Functions@{ub}@{uu}


    The functions have also the RXASL_FunctionName and
    RXASLFunctionName forms to avoid conflicts with functions
    from other libraries.

    - Requesters -
    @{"ReqFile       " LINK "ReqFile"       }   @{"ReqFont       " LINK "ReqFont"    }  @{"ReScreen      " LINK "ReqScreen"}

    - Preferences -
    @{"GetAslPrefs   " LINK "GetAslPrefs"   }   @{"SetAslPrefs   " LINK "SetAslPrefs"}

    - Various -
    @{"GetRxAslString" LINK "GetRxAslString"}   @{"Help          " LINK "Help"       }

@EndNode

@Node "ReqFile" "RxAsl Functions - ReqFile"

  @{b}ReqFile@{ub} - shows a file requester


  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = ReqFile(stem)
    <stem/V>


  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Shows a file requester.

    In @{i}stem@{ui} you may set the fields:

    o @{u}@{b}Window@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}Window@{ub}/S
        This is a name of a RxMUI Window object or a RxWiz
        SURFACE/WINDOW pair. If the window is found, it is put to
        sleep.

      . @{b}PubScreen@{ub}/S
        This is the name of a public screen. If it is found, the
        requester is opened on it, otherwise, the requester is
        opened on the default public screen if and only if
        FALLBACK is 1.

      . @{b}FallBack@{ub}/B
        See PUBSCREEN, default 0

      . @{b}SleepWindow@{ub}/B

      . @{b}NTScreenToFront@{ub}/B
        The screen, the requester opens on, is put to front by
        default. Setting it to 0 causes the screen to not be put
        to front.

      . @{b}Activate@{ub}/B
        Only asl.library V45 (AmigaOS 3.9)

    o @{u}@{b}Text@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}Title@{ub}/S

      . @{b}PositiveText@{ub}/S

      . @{b}NegativeText@{ub}/S

    o @{u}@{b}Initial settings@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}LeftEdge@{ub}/N
        Default 0

      . @{b}TopEdge@{ub}/N
        Default 0

      . @{b}Width@{ub}/N
        Default 50% of screen width

      . @{b}Height@{ub}/N
        Default 50% of screen height

      . @{b}File@{ub}/S

      . @{b}Drawer@{ub}/S

      . @{b}Pattern@{ub}/S

      . @{b}ShowVolumes@{ub}/B
        Only asl.library V44 (AmigaOS 3.5)

    o @{u}@{b}Options@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}DoSaveMode@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoMultiSelect@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoPatterns@{ub}/B

      . @{b}NoEmpty@{ub}/B
        If set and the user enters an empty file name the result
        of ReqFile() will be -1, like the user pressed "Cancel"
        button if not set and the user enters an empty file name,
        an empty file name is returned; it is only valid for file
        requester not for drawer requester, because empty drawer
        name means CurrentDir.

    o @{u}@{b}Filtering@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}DrawersOnly@{ub}/B

      . @{b}FilterFunc@{ub}/S
        This is an ARexx macro called for each entry in the
        requester, before the entry is shown.
        The macro is called as a function with argument:
        - entry name
        - drawer name
        - struct FileInfoBlock pointer

        If and only if the function returns 0, the entry is not
        shown (e.g. if the function fails, the entry is shown).

      . @{b}FilterString@{ub}/B
        FilterFunc is a string-inline function.

      . @{b}RejectIcons@{ub}/B

      . @{b}RejectPattern@{ub}/S

      . @{b}AcceptPattern@{ub}/S

      . @{b}FilterDrawers@{ub}/B

    o @{u}@{b}Sorting@{ub}@{uu} Only asl.library V44 (AmigaOS 3.5)

      . @{b}SortBy@{ub}/M
        A number or one of:
        - NAME
        - DATE
        - SIZE

      . @{b}SortDrawers@{ub}/N
        A number or one of:
        - FIRST
        - MIX
        - LAST

      . @{b}SortOrder@{ub}/N
        A number or one of:
        - ASCEND
        - DESCEND


    The function writes in @{i}stem@{ui}:

    o @{b}LeftEdge@{ub}/N

    o @{b}TopEdge@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Width@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Height@{ub}/N

    o @{b}File@{ub}/S

    o @{b}Drawer@{ub}/S

    o @{b}Pattern@{ub}/S

    o @{b}SortBy@{ub}/N
      Only asl.library V44 (AmigaOS 3.5)

    o @{b}SortDrawers@{ub}/N
      Only asl.library V44 (AmigaOS 3.5)

    o @{b}SortOrder@{ub}/N
      Only asl.library V44 (AmigaOS 3.5)

    o If DoMultiselect is set to 1,  the number of the files
      selected is in @{b}NUM@{ub} (and in @{b}NUMARGS@{ub} for compatibility)
      and the selected files are in @{i}stem@{ui}.0, ...
      They may be read with:
          do i=0 to stem.num-1
              say stem.i
          end


  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    stem - an ARexx stem name


  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - an integer:
            o -1 the user exit from the requester
            o  0 OK
            o >0 error code - use @{"GetRxAslString" LINK "GetRxAslString"} to get the string
                 @{b}RxAslErr@{ub} is also set to the field name that caused the error.

@EndNode

@Node "ReqFont" "RxAsl Functions - ReqFont"

  @{b}ReqFont@{ub} - shows a font requester


  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = ReqFont(stem)
    <stem/V>


  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Shows a font requester.

    In @{i}stem@{ui} you may set the fields:

    o @{u}@{b}Window@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}Window@{ub}/S
        This is a name of a RxMUI Window object or a RxWiz
        SURFACE/WINDOW pair. If the window is found, it is put to
        sleep.

      . @{b}PubScreen@{ub}/S
        This is the name of a public screen. If it is found, the
        requester is opened on it, otherwise, the requester is
        opened on the default public screen if and only if
        FALLBACK is 1.

      . @{b}FallBack@{ub}/B
        See PUBSCREEN, default 0

      . @{b}SleepWindow@{ub}/B

      . @{b}NTScreenToFront@{ub}/B
        The screen, the requester opens on, is put to front by
        default. Setting it to 0 causes the screen to not be put
        to front.

      . @{b}Activate@{ub}/B
        Only asl.library V45 (AmigaOS 3.9)

    o @{u}@{b}Text@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}Title@{ub}/S

      . @{b}PositiveText@{ub}/S

      . @{b}NegativeText@{ub}/S

      . @{b}SampleText@{ub}/S
        Only asl.library V45 (AmigaOS 3.9)

    o @{u}@{b}Initial settings@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}LeftEdge@{ub}/N
        Default 0

      . @{b}TopEdge@{ub}/N
        Default 0

      . @{b}Width@{ub}/N
        Default 50% of screen width

      . @{b}Height@{ub}/N
        Default 50% of screen height

      . @{b}Name@{ub}/S

      . @{b}Size@{ub}/N

      . @{b}Style@{ub}/M
        A number or a combination of:
        - NORMAL
        - UNDERLINE
        - BOLD
        - ITALIC

      . @{b}Flags@{ub}/N

      . @{b}FrontPen@{ub}/N

      . @{b}BackPen@{ub}/N

      . @{b}DrawMode@{ub}/M
        A number or one of:
        - JAM1
        - JAM2
        - COMPLEMENT

    o @{u}@{b}Options@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}DoFrontPen@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoBackPen@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoStyle@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoDrawMode@{ub}/B

    o @{u}@{b}Filtering@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}FixedWidthOnly@{ub}/B

      . @{b}MinHeight@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MaxHeight@{ub}/N

      . @{b}FilterFunc@{ub}/S

       This is an ARexx macro called for each entry in the
       requester, before the entry is shown.
       The macro is called as a function with argument:
       - entry name
       - YSize
       - struct TextAttr pointer

       If and only if the function returns 0, the entry is not
       shown (e.g. if the function fails, the entry is shown).

      . @{b}FilterString@{ub}/B
        FilterFunc is a string-inline function.

      . @{b}MaxFrontPen@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MaxBackPen@{ub}/N


    The function writes in @{i}stem@{ui}:

    o @{b}LeftEdge@{ub}/N

    o @{b}TopEdge@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Width@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Height@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Name@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Size@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Style@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Flags@{ub}/N

    o @{b}DrawMode@{ub}/N

    o @{b}FrontPen@{ub}/N

    o @{b}BackPen@{ub}/N


  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    stem - an ARexx stem name


  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - an integer:
            o -1 the user exit from the requester
            o  0 OK
            o >0 error code - use @{"GetRxAslString" LINK "GetRxAslString"} to get the string
                 @{b}RxAslErr@{ub} is also set to the field name that caused the error.

@EndNode

@Node "ReqScreen" "RxAsl Functions - ReqScreen"

  @{b}ReqScreen@{ub} - shows a screen requester


  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = ReqScreen(stem)
    <stem/V>


  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Shows a screen requester.

    In @{i}stem@{ui} you may set the fields:

    o @{u}@{b}Window@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}Window@{ub}/S
        This is a name of a RxMUI Window object or a RxWiz
        SURFACE/WINDOW pair. If the window is found, it is put to
        sleep.

      . @{b}PubScreen@{ub}/S
        This is the name of a public screen. If it is found, the
        requester is opened on it, otherwise, the requester is
        opened on the default public screen if and only if
        FALLBACK is 1.

      . @{b}FallBack@{ub}/B
        See PUBSCREEN. Default 0

      . @{b}SleepWindow@{ub}/B

      . @{b}NTScreenToFront@{ub}/B
        The screen, the requester opens on, is put to front by
        default. Setting it to 0 causes the screen to not be put
        to front.

      . @{b}Activate@{ub}/B
        Only asl.library V45 (AmigaOS 3.9)

    o @{u}@{b}Text@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}Title@{ub}/S

      . @{b}PositiveText@{ub}/S

      . @{b}NegativeText@{ub}/S

    o @{u}@{b}Initial settings@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}LeftEdge@{ub}/N
        Default 0

      . @{b}TopEdge@{ub}/N
        Default 0

      . @{b}Width@{ub}/N
        Default 50% of screen width

      . @{b}Height@{ub}/N
        Default 50% of screen height

      . @{b}DisplayID@{ub}/N

      . @{b}DisplayWidth@{ub}/N

      . @{b}DisplayHeight@{ub}/N

      . @{b}DisplayDepth@{ub}/N

      . @{b}Overscan@{ub}/N
        A number or one of:
        - TEXT
        - STANDARD
        - MAX
        - VIDEO

      . @{b}AutoScroll@{ub}/B

      . @{b}InfoOpened@{ub}/B

      . @{b}InfoLeftEdge@{ub}/N

      . @{b}InfoTopEdge@{ub}/N

    o @{u}@{b}Options@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}DoWidth@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoHeight@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoDepth@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoOverscan@{ub}/B

      . @{b}DoAutoScroll@{ub}/B

    o @{u}@{b}Filtering@{ub}@{uu}

      . @{b}PropertyFlags@{ub}/N

      . @{b}PropertyMask@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MinWidth@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MaxWidth@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MinHeight@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MaxHeight@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MinDepth@{ub}/N

      . @{b}MaxDepth@{ub}/N

      . @{b}FilterFunc@{ub}/S

        This is an ARexx macro called for each entry in the
        requester, before the entry is shown.
        The macro is called as a function with argument:
        - screen mode
        - struct ScreenModeRequester pointer

        If and only if the function returns 0, the entry is not
        shown (e.g. if the function fails, the entry is shown).

      . @{b}FilterString@{ub}/B
        FilterFunc is a string-inline function.


    The function writes in @{i}stem@{ui}:

    o @{b}LeftEdge@{ub}/N

    o @{b}TopEdge@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Width@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Height@{ub}/N

    o @{b}DisplayID@{ub}/N

    o @{b}DisplayWidth@{ub}/N

    o @{b}DisplayHeight@{ub}/N

    o @{b}DisplayDepth@{ub}/N

    o @{b}Overscan@{ub}/N

    o @{b}AutoScroll@{ub}/B

    o @{b}InfoOpened@{ub}/B

    o @{b}InfoLeftEdge@{ub}/B

    o @{b}InfoTopEdge@{ub}/B

    o @{b}BitmapWidth@{ub}/B

    o @{b}BitmapHeight@{ub}/B


  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    stem - an ARexx stem name


  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - an integer:
            o -1 the user exit from the requester
            o  0 OK
            o >0 error code - use @{"GetRxAslString" LINK "GetRxAslString"} to get the string
                 @{b}RxAslErr@{ub} is also set to the field name that caused the error.

@EndNode

@Node "GetAslPrefs" "RxAsl Functions - GetAslPrefs"

  @{b}GetAslPrefs@{ub} - reads asl.library preferences


  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = GetAslPrefs(stem)
    <stem/V>


  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Reads asl.library V45+ preferences. Note that the function
    reads asl.library and not ENV: or ENVARC: preferences. That
    means preferences read by this function may differ from what
    reported by SYS:Prefs/ASL.

    The function writes in @{i}stem@{ui}:

    o @{u}@{b}SizePosition@{ub}@{uu}/N
      Don't care about it.

    o @{u}@{b}SortBy@{ub}@{uu}/N
      . 0 - Name
      . 1 - Size
      . 2 - Date

    o @{u}@{b}SortByStr@{ub}@{uu}/S
      . Name - 0
      . Size - 1
      . Date - 2

    o @{u}@{b}SortDrawers@{ub}@{uu}/N
      . 0 - First
      . 1 - Mix
      . 2 - Last

    o @{u}@{b}SortDrawersStr@{ub}@{uu}/S
      . First - 0
      . Mix   - 1
      . Last  - 2

    o @{u}@{b}SortOrder@{ub}@{uu}/N
      . 0 - Ascend
      . 1 - Descend

    o @{u}@{b}SortOrderStr@{ub}@{uu}/S
      . Ascend  - 0
      . Descend - 1

    o @{u}@{b}Position@{ub}@{uu}/N
      . 0 - Default
      . 1 - CenterWindow
      . 2 - CenterScreen
      . 3 - WindowPosition
      . 4 - ScreenPosition
      . 5 - CenterMouse

    o @{u}@{b}PositionStr@{ub}@{uu}/S
      . Default        - 0
      . CenterWindow   - 1
      . CenterScreen   - 2
      . WindowPosition - 3
      . ScreenPosition - 4
      . CenterMouse    - 5

    o @{u}@{b}Size@{ub}@{uu}/N
      . Default  - 0
      . Relative - 1

    o @{u}@{b}SizeStr@{ub}@{uu}/S
      . 0 - Default
      . 1 - Relative

    o @{u}@{b}Override@{ub}@{uu}/B

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeLeft@{ub}@{uu}/N

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeTop@{ub}@{uu}/N

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeWidth@{ub}@{uu}/N

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeHeight@{ub}@{uu}/N


  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    stem - an ARexx stem name


  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - an ARexx boolean


  @{b}See@{ub}
    @{"SetAslPrefs" LINK "SetAslPrefs"}

@EndNode

@Node "SetAslPrefs" "RxAsl Functions - SetAslPrefs"

  @{b}SetAslPrefs@{ub} - writes asl.library preferences


  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    res = SetAslPrefs(stem)
    <stem/V>


  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Writes asl.library V45+ preferences. Note that the function
    writes asl.library and not ENV: or ENVARC: preferences.

    In @{i}stem@{ui} you may set the fields:

    o @{u}@{b}SortBy@{ub}@{uu}/M
      An integer or one of:
      . Name  - 0
      . Size  - 1
      . Date  - 2

    o @{u}@{b}SortDrawers@{ub}@{uu}/M
      An integer or one of:
      . First - 0
      . Mix   - 1
      . Last  - 2

    o @{u}@{b}SortOrder@{ub}@{uu}/M
      An integer or one of:
      . Ascend  - 0
      . Descend - 1

    o @{u}@{b}Position@{ub}@{uu}/M
      An integer or one of:
      . Default        - 0
      . CenterWindow   - 1
      . CenterScreen   - 2
      . WindowPosition - 3
      . ScreenPosition - 4
      . CenterMouse    - 5

    o @{u}@{b}Size@{ub}@{uu}/M
      An integer or one of:
      . Default  - 0
      . Relative - 1

    o @{u}@{b}Override@{ub}@{uu}/B

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeLeft@{ub}@{uu}/N
      0<=x<=2048

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeTop@{ub}@{uu}/N
      0<=x<=2048

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeWidth@{ub}@{uu}/N
      25<=x<=100

    o @{u}@{b}RelativeHeight@{ub}@{uu}/N
      25<=x<=100


  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    stem - an ARexx stem name


  @{b}Result@{ub}
    res - a boolean


  @{b}See@{ub}
    @{"GetAslPrefs" LINK "GetAslPrefs"}

@EndNode

@Node "GetRxAslString" "RxAsl Functions - GetRxAslString"

  @{b}GetRxAslString@{ub} - returns a localized RxAsl string


  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    string = GetRxAslString(id)
    <id/N>


  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Returns a localized RxAsl string.

    @{i}id@{ui} is one of:
    o 51  [NO_MEM]        too few memory
    o 52  [ARG_MISS]      required argument missing
    o 53  [BAD_NUMBER]    bad number
    o 54  [BAD_VALUE]     bad value
    o 55  [BAD_PATTERN]   bad pattern
    o 56  [NO_WINDOW]     window not found
    o 57  [NO_SCREEN]     public screen not found


  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    id - an integer


  @{b}Result@{ub}
    string - a RxAsl localized string

@EndNode

@Node "Help" "RxAsl Functions - Help"

  @{b}help@{ub} - returns a RxAsl function help strings


  @{b}Synopsis@{ub}
    string = Help(funName)
    <funName/S>


  @{b}Function@{ub}
    Returns the arguments types mask of the function
    @{i}funName@{ui}.


  @{b}Inputs@{ub}
    funName - a RxAsl function name


  @{b}Result@{ub}
    string - a help string

@EndNode

